# CLAUDE.md — Android + KMP (shared domain + networking)

## Always apply these skills

- android-kmp-shared-module
- android-kmp-ktor-serialization
- android-presentation-mvi
- android-compose-ui
- android-data-layer
- android-error-handling
- android-di-koin
- android-coroutines-flow
- android-navigation
- android-testing

## Module rules

- `commonMain` must have zero `android.*` imports
- Repository interfaces in `commonMain`; Room/SQLDelight impls in `androidMain`
- Ktor `HttpClient` factory in `commonMain`; engine (`OkHttp`/`Darwin`) injected per platform
- `expect`/`actual` only for genuinely platform-divergent behaviour

## Patterns to follow

- Domain models: plain Kotlin `data class` — no Android annotations
- Network: `safeApiCall` wrapping every Ktor call → `Result<T, DataError.Network>`
- State: `StateFlow` in shared code; KMP-NativeCoroutines for iOS consumption
- ViewModel: Android `ViewModel` on Android; `CommonViewModel` base for shared logic

## Do not

- Put `android.*`, `androidx.*`, or `com.google.*` imports in `commonMain`
- Use Room in `commonMain` — use SQLDelight or keep Room in `androidMain`
- Use `Dispatchers.Main` directly — inject dispatcher
- Use `GlobalScope`
